"{\"abstract\":\"Topic models with sparsity enhancement have been proven to be effective at learn- ing discriminative and coherent latent top- ics of short texts, which is critical to many scientific and engineering applica- tions. However, the extensions of these models require carefully tailored graphi- cal models and re-deduced inference al- gorithms, limiting their variations and ap- plications. We propose a novel sparsity- enhanced topic model, Neural Sparse Top- ical Coding (NSTC) base on a sparsity- enhanced topic model called Sparse Top- ical Coding (STC). It focuses on replac- ing the complex inference process with the back propagation, which makes the model easy to explore extensions. Moreover, the external semantic information of words in word embeddings is incorporated to im- prove the representation of short texts. To illustrate the flexibility offered by the neu- ral network based framework, we present three extensions base on NSTC without re-deduced inference algorithms. Experi- ments on Web Snippet and 20Newsgroups datasets demonstrate that our models out- perform existing methods.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"145053991\",\"name\":\"Min Peng\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/145053991\"},{\"authorId\":\"145229872\",\"name\":\"Qianqian Xie\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/145229872\"},{\"authorId\":\"48017500\",\"name\":\"H. Wang\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/48017500\"},{\"authorId\":\"34853026\",\"name\":\"Y. Zhang\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/34853026\"},{\"authorId\":\"1821099\",\"name\":\"Xiuzhen Zhang\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1821099\"},{\"authorId\":\"2555230\",\"name\":\"Jimin Huang\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/2555230\"},{\"authorId\":\"49209832\",\"name\":\"Gang Tian\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/49209832\"}],\"citationVelocity\":6,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{